Dark matter influences flight of space probes
For years, a mysterious phenomenon in research has been causing infidelity: Dark matter influences the speed of space probes during so-called swing-by maneuvers.
Experts fear that Albert Einstein's general theory of relativity could not be quite right.
For almost 18 years, the space probe "Ulysses" flew through space.
