The drivers, who can become backward because of the alcohol level, will need to install the `Alcolock'.
The Authority orders that the driver, who had three official penalties for alcohol levels, installs this system in his car, which forbids him to start the car in the drunk state. If he is alcoholized, the car does not jump on.
The initiative was announced last month in June and is now part of the report of the Public Prosecutor General. According to its information, it is a pilot project which will take a year.
The purpose is to re-socialise the driver, which is why he receives a course for re-education of traffic behaviour.
Apart from the State Attorney General's experience, the Ministry of Transport and the Foundation of the Technical Institute for the Safety of Motor Vehicles will also participate.
According to statistics, between 30-75% of drivers, who were shown to be under alcohol influence more than once because of driving, are taxed again.
The `alcolock' would prevent this because it is a system connected to the car, it measures the alcohol content in the air exhausted and prevents car start when the driver has performed alcohol tests; or if an alcohol concentration is determined which is higher than permitted.
It costs more than 1 000 euros, the costs are borne by the person who imposes the penalty.
In this context, a study carried out in the United States in 2007 showed that cars equipped with these devices prevented up to 65% of the regulatory infringements in the first year after its introduction.
In Spain, it is estimated that 115 lives could be saved annually.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to attack this behaviour before it became a criminal offence.
And in order to facilitate their implementation, a legislative reform can be implemented in the ordinary way, and yet a reform of the basic law is required, which is necessary for the prosecution process.
The equipment is still available in the Spanish markets, in no store, although it has already been installed in some commercial vehicles and vehicles of public transport.
Tomorrow, the House of Deputies will vote for the initiative of the Spanish Socialist Workers' Party, which proposes to install this system in school buses, which has already been done in France.
